The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for learning locomotion skills, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also explores the impact of different action parameterizations on learning and performance, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves processing high-dimensional state descriptors. Additionally, the paper evaluates the policies in terms of robustness and motion quality, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
